{
  "info": {
    "name": "Users CRUD API",
    "description": "CRUD endpoints for the `users` and `companies` tables with RBAC authorization.\n\n## Setup\n1. Set the `baseUrl` variable (default: `http://localhost:3000`)\n2. Run **Login (Superadmin)** or **Login (Operator Admin)** first to auto-set the `token` variable\n3. All requests require `{{token}}` from the collection variables\n\n## Roles\n- **superadmin**: full access (`*:*`)\n- **operator_admin**: user CRUD + company read/update (own) + resources within company\n- **operator_staff**: read-only + own profile (no company or user access)\n- **tourist / association**: no user:* or company permissions",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "userId",
      "value": "1",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "companyId",
      "value": "1",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "otherCompanyUserId",
      "value": "999",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Authentication endpoints to obtain JWT tokens for testing.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login (Superadmin)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.success && res.data && res.data.token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', res.data.token);",
                  "    pm.test('Token saved to collection variables', function () {",
                  "        pm.expect(pm.collectionVariables.get('token')).to.not.be.empty;",
                  "    });",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has success envelope', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(res.success).to.eql(true);",
                  "    pm.expect(res.data).to.have.property('token');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"identifier\": \"superadmin_seed\",\n  \"password\": \"superadmin123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Login as superadmin to get a JWT token. Has `*:*` (all permissions). The token is automatically saved to the `token` collection variable."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (Operator Admin – user:* perms)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.success && res.data && res.data.token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', res.data.token);",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"identifier\": \"operator_seed\",\n  \"password\": \"operator123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Login as operator admin. Has user:create/read/update/delete + resources CRUD (company-scoped). When creating users, new users auto-get operator_staff role + caller's company_id."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (Operator Staff – no user perms)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.success && res.data && res.data.token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', res.data.token);",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"identifier\": \"operator_staff_seed\",\n  \"password\": \"staff123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Login as operator staff. Has NO user:* permissions — expect 403 on users endpoints. Only has profile:read/update + read-only access to resources."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (Association – no user perms)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.success && res.data && res.data.token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', res.data.token);",
